cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for RGB-D and RGB semantic segmentation. It also involves some aspects of artificial intelligence (AI) and robotics (RO) in terms of using depth information for better segmentation. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) falls under the multimedia (MM) category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.RO, and cs.MM.
